# Decision Trees & Random Forests

# Objective
Learn tree-based models for classification.

# Dataset
Heart Disease Dataset
link - https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/johnsmith88/heart-disease-dataset

# Steps Performed
- Data loading and preprocessing
- Trained Decision Tree Classifier
- Visualized Decision Tree
- Controlled overfitting using max_depth
- Trained Random Forest model
- Compared accuracy
- Analyzed feature importance
- Performed cross-validation

# Results
- Decision Tree Accuracy: 0.7804878048780488 %
- Random Forest Accuracy: 0.9853658536585366 %
- Cross-validation Accuracy: [1.  1.   1.   1. 0.98536585]%

# Key Learnings
- Decision trees can overfit easily
- Random forest improves performance using ensemble learning
- Feature importance helps interpret models

# Tools Used
- Python
- Scikit-learn
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
